<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kind of embarassing... we haven't been to Chardok in ages, since it was revamped.  We regularily take down Vind/Statue/Rhag and stuff....  but the queen handed us our maximuses twice in a row last night. /cry<P>It seems like the queen's AE now includes some kind of knock back.  Our tactic of pinning her to the wall doesn't work.<P>Can you good folks post your queen pulling/fighting tactics that you are using these days since she was buffed a bit.  We like to fight her in her room because she gates.<P>Last two things that worked for us was having Bard harmonize queen, pull some guards.  Rinse repeat until she's almost alone.  Then have enchanter go invis pretarget some mobs for mez.  DA person runs in, positions queen in a good spot and everyone changes in.  Mobs mezzed, Queen killed, end of the story.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corynthia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Me guild have taken the Queen down twice after the Chardok Revision and AFAIK we used the old method of clearing the room, leaving her alone and then rushing in with everyone clicking their damage discicple and nuking like hell.  that got her killed in 2 sec flat both times.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7173" TARGET=_blank>Corynthia</A><BR>High Priestess of Brell<BR>Keeper of the Holy Ale<BR>United Kingdom<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Are her guards still mezzable?  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have been on countless failed raids to take out this Queen.  The ones I have seen work, monk pulls out extras and we kill in King Room.  Sacrifical Paladin throws up DB to take the first AE and then rush it - clerics stay in the hallway.<P>A method I heard has worked using a non-KoS person.  A monk pulls the whole room and FD's.  The non-kos person hails the queen.  The queen will answer and the others go back to the places.  Raids attacks.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">varthdadur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've only killed her once.  We pulled her to the king room and then had 3 mage fire pets beat her up while 2 clerics healed and everyone else watched.  I think I CH'd twice.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Perplex</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Due to lack of patience, we usually use the brute force approach to this one.<P>What we do is invis up, and go into her room fully popped, tanks positioned around her, casters near the door and outside AE range. <P>MA first drops invis, everyone Disc/Nuke the crap out of her right off the bat while chanters deal with the guards. Clerics use either group CHs or word of restoration. She dies pretty fast with all hell being released on her. After she's dead, deal with the mezzed guards.<P><P>------------------<BR><BR>Perplex Cerebrum<BR>High Priest of The Shadow Order<BR>Lanys T'Vyll</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <A HREF="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=10089.topic" TARGET=_blank>http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=10089.topic</A> <P><BR>/nod<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 54th Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Tailor (163)Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) <BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Qamen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Our guild will use this method:<P>First find all of the enchanter (3 or more) invis up, and come down to the queen's room (all mob can't see invis  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif">). Then enchanters mark up which queen's guard which they will mez. After all confirmed, call all ppl invis up and come down. Find a brave pally(must die :lol) go to queen's platform, when he open his DA up, all enchanter mez their mark up guard at same time. Finally all people open offensive and <B>CHARGE !</B><P>------------------<BR>by Qamen<BR>High Priest in FRo server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for the advice.  We went back to the old tried and true way of doing it and cut down the huge number of people we took, and it worked out just fine.<P>1) dispatched King and his guards quickly<BR>2) Had level 60 bard lull the queen<BR>3) pulled some guards (3-4 came)<BR>4) invisible enchanters pretarget remaining mobs<BR>5) Had paladin run in and DA behind the queen<BR>6) Everyone runs in and massively zergs.  Everyone nukes, even clerics.  Casters stay at the doorway (no ae).<P>We had 0 deaths.  Our first queen raid with absolutely no deaths!<P>I even stunned her once!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zyphyr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Instead of sending a suicide paladin, send in a level 49 magician fire pet... It will hold her in the room just fine, it will get her to fire off her first AE with nobody else in the room, and it is immune to the AE so it lives long enough for the other people to charge in after the initial AE.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Our suicide Paladin didn't have the decency to die.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">  He survived the battle just fine.  But the pet idea is excellent.  </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
